The wireless card has "NMP-3601 LFP-1.00" and a smiley face silkscreened on it.
===Reviews=== *[http://www.smallnetbuilder.com/content/view/30099/109/ On '''SmallNetBuilder''']<small> :The large silver device in the top right is the PCMCIA slot for the WWAN card. :The board is based on a chipset manufactured by [http://www.cavium.com Cavium], :which utilizes [http://www.cnusers.org/wrapper/Product_table.html ''Cavium's Nitrox Security Processor series'']. :The board uses passive cooling, so it is silent, and has :128MB of RAM plus 16MB of Flash Memory. </small>
